qas.question: From where did Cerón attempt to cross the Pacific Ocean?
What did Cerón name the islands from which people threw rocks at his vessel?
What was the name given to the islands reached by Cerón in October of 1529?
What are two possible modern names for the islands called Los Jardines by Cerón?
Who was in charge of the ship named Florida?
What name did Cerón give to the island that might have been Ujelang?
What group of islands might have been Bikini Atoll or Enewetak?
How long did Cerón spend on Los Jardines?

context: On September 21, 1529, <a0_0><a5_0>Álvaro de Saavedra Cerón<a5_0/><a0_0/> commanded the Spanish ship Florida, on his second attempt to recross the Pacific from <a1_0><a6_0>the Maluku Islands<a6_0/><a1_0/>. He stood off a group of islands from which local inhabitants hurled stones at his ship. These islands, which he named "<a2_0><a7_0>Los Pintados<a7_0/><a2_0/>", may have been Ujelang. On October 1, he found another group of islands where he went ashore for <a9_0>eight days<a9_0/>, exchanged gifts with the local inhabitants and took on water. These islands, which he named "<a3_0><a8_0>Los Jardines<a8_0/><a3_0/>", may have been <a4_0>Enewetak or Bikini Atoll<a4_0/>.
